Get root with Sudo -i:                                                  #
apt install html-xml-utils:                                             #
apt install wget:                                                       #
apt install w3m:                                                        #
#########################################################################
                                                                        #
You can also create an alias and call this as a common command in       #
konsole at any time.                                                    #
                                                                        #
https://www.tecmint.com/create-alias-in-linux/                          #
https://phoenixnap.com/kb/linux-alias-command                           #
#########################################################################

Steam Launch Options relative commands
-fullscreen - Forces the engine to start in fullscreen mode.
-windowed or -sw - Forces the engine to start in windowed mode.
-w [width] - Forces the engine to start with resolution set to [width].

-h [height] - Forces the engine to start with resolution set to [height]. 
This launch option does not need to be set in the presence of -w. 
The width value will determine the height automatically.
###########################################################################
Myself, I created a directory at /home/username/.steam/resources/shellscript/
and place scripts like these into it.
My directory structure is:
.steam/resources/
.steam/resources/banners
.steam/resources/icons
.steam/resources/shellscript
Then they can easily be used by steam and avoid cluttering your home folder etc
